<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3831/4: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Belden</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-05T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 5,
                                    1920—noon.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 6—1:45
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>25. Department’s number 32, March 29, noon. Decree has not been
                                issued. The President has instructed Haitian Chargé d’Affaires at
                                Washington to confer with Financial Adviser relative thereto.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Belden</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>